issue.body:
It seems like when waking up from a suspend, winit does not properly restore the window size.

The following image shows two windows that were the same size before suspend after waking up:

![](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/318501/69576422-196d1b00-0f81-11ea-9ef4-683bde906d88.png)

The following log messages seem relevant:
```
[2019-11-25 12:57] [INFO] Device pixel ratio: 2
[2019-11-25 12:57] [INFO] Width: 1600, Height: 1200
[2019-11-25 12:57] [INFO] PTY Dimensions: Line(36) x Column(114)
[2019-11-25 12:57] [INFO] glutin event: NewEvents(Init)
[2019-11-25 12:57] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(75497474))), event: Resized(LogicalSize { width: 800.0, height: 600.0 }) }
[2019-11-25 12:57] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(75497474))), event: Moved(LogicalPosition { x: 0.0, y: 437.0 }) }
[2019-11-25 12:57] [INFO] Width: 1600, Height: 1200
[2019-11-25 12:57] [INFO] Width: 1600, Height: 1200
[2019-11-25 12:58] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(75497474))), event: HiDpiFactorChanged(1.0) }
[2019-11-25 12:58] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(75497474))), event: Resized(LogicalSize { width: 1600.0, height: 1200.0 }) }
[2019-11-25 12:58] [INFO] Width: 1600, Height: 1200
[2019-11-25 12:58] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(75497474))), event: Resized(LogicalSize { width: 400.0, height: 300.0 }) }
[2019-11-25 12:58] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(75497474))), event: HiDpiFactorChanged(1.0) }
[2019-11-25 12:58] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(75497474))), event: Resized(LogicalSize { width: 800.0, height: 600.0 }) }
[2019-11-25 12:58] [INFO] Width: 800, Height: 600
[2019-11-25 12:58] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(75497474))), event: Resized(LogicalSize { width: 200.0, height: 150.0 }) }
[2019-11-25 12:58] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(75497474))), event: HiDpiFactorChanged(1.0) }
[2019-11-25 12:58] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(75497474))), event: Resized(LogicalSize { width: 400.0, height: 300.0 }) }
[2019-11-25 12:58] [INFO] Width: 400, Height: 300
[2019-11-25 12:58] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(75497474))), event: Resized(LogicalSize { width: 100.0, height: 75.0 }) }
[2019-11-25 12:58] [INFO] Width: 100, Height: 75
```

The following comment from @nixpulvis might be relevant:

> Notable each time the font size is reported it divides the width and height by 2, but then finally doesn't report the font, and divides by 4. It seems there's more wake up events after that, but it doesn't get any smaller.

The DPR at startup was also reported as `2`. So continuous division by two while reporting a DPR change to `1` seems like it could be the problem. So maybe incorrect DPR detection?

This was originally reported to Alacritty in https://github.com/jwilm/alacritty/issues/3022.
